This report was received on 26NOV2014 from a consumer via the (b) (6)  
 and has not been medically confirmed.  A 58-year-old male patient initiated H P Acthar (corticotropin) gel, 
80 units twice weekly via injection, for treatment of membranous nephropathy on 02OCT2014.  It was reported that 
the patient has been in the hospital with newly diagnosed colitis.  Additionally, the patient's appetite increases after 
injections.
Additional information was received on 03DEC2014 from a consumer via the (b) (6)  
  The patient continues to be hospitalized and an infection in the patient's intestines is suspected 
(the lab results are not yet completed).  He has an elevated white blood cell count.  No additional information was 
available at the time of reporting.
